                <solution>
                    <p>
                        To find the area of the pentagon above, we can use should identify the side length and the apothem.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                       <m>\text{Apothem} = 12.4 \, \text{ft}\, ,\text{Side length} = 18\, \text{ ft} </m>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        The perimeter of the pentagon is:<m>5 \times 18\, \text{ ft}=90 \, \text{ft}</m>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Using the formula for the area of a regular pentagon:
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <md>
                            <mrow> \text{Area} =\amp \frac{1}{2} \times \text{Perimeter} \times  \text{apothem}</mrow>
                            <mrow> =\amp \frac{1}{2} \times 90 \times 12.4</mrow>
                            <mrow> =\amp  45 \times 12.4</mrow>
                            <mrow> =\amp  558 \, \text{ft}^2</mrow>
                        </md>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Therefore, the area of the pentagon is <m>{\color{blue}558 \, \text{ft}^2}</m>.
                    </p>
                </solution>
